hikoi
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a walk, march (popularised in Eng. use when applied to the march to Waitangi, on Waitangi Day, 6 February, 1984).
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [Ma. <b>hikoi</B> step out, plod, pace, stepping (netball)] cf. P.M. Ryan Dict. Modern Maori (1995) 52.
